NULL,'Artist Panel Talk[tagdivider]Cole Lu ⌁ Na Buqi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'cole-lu-na-buqi',NULL,'2020-04-18 19:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Zoom online meeting																					',_binary '<div class=\"centered\"><a href=\"https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/qyz2-iYlKx11upVJN1l9tw\" target=\"_blank\">活动信息</a></div>[imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00015.png\" alt=\"Cole Lu presenting Animal Fancy\"><figcaption class=\"caption caption-roman\">Cole Lu presenting Animal Fancy</figcaption></figure>[endimagedivider][imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00016.png\" alt=\"Na Buqi - 漂浮的情节\"><figcaption class=\"caption caption-roman\">Na Buqi - 漂浮的情节</figcaption></figure>[endimagedivider][sectiondivider]',_binary '\r\n																								'),(17,1,'2021-02-01 07:56:51','2021-02-01 08:52:16',NULL,'Artist Panel Talk[tagdivider]Jakob Kudsk Steensen ⌁ Camille Henrot[subtitledivider]系统构建：材料组织和叙事',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'jakob-kudsk-steensen-camille-henrot',NULL,'2020-12-19 19:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Zoom online meeting',_binary '<div class=\"centered\"><a href=\"https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/lv9umWSvr5l07dIDTqPlHA\" target=\"_blank\">活动信息</a></div>[sectiondivider]Jakob Kudsk Steensen[sectiontitledivider]Jakob Kudsk Steensen 是一位丹麦艺术家，目前工作生活于纽约，他通过3D动画、声音和沉浸式装置来讲述被忽视的生态系统和被遗忘的自然历史的故事，他关注想象力、技术和生态的相互交融，研究人们如何在心理和情感层面上与气候联系在一起。Kudsk Steensen的很多作品都根植于这样一种社会学观点：我们不再生活在一个能够以过去预测未来的时代，科技和自然正以比我们所能理解的更快、更剧烈方式在改变。他的作品基于广泛的实地考察，同时与野外生物学家、作曲家和作家合作，以此开发出VR和视频装置，将物理的、虚拟的、真实的和想象的景观结合在混合现实装置中，创作出对被忽视的自然现象的诗意诠释，并邀请观众进入新的生态现实。Kudsk Steensen 入围2019年威尼斯双年展未来一代艺术奖（Future Generation Art Prize），在2019年科技与电影电影节上获得了最佳动画制作设计奖等。Kudsk Steensen 目前是法国 Luma Arles 艺术中心的驻馆艺术家，他在那里记录坎格尔(Camargue)湿地的藻类和结晶过程。<div><br>Jakob Kudsk Steensen, a Danish artist based in New York, brings together physical, virtual, real, and imagined landscapes in mixed-reality installations. He creates location-specific artworks that tell stories of overlooked ecosystems and forgotten natural histories. He is concerned with how imagination, technology, and ecology intertwine, investigating how people relate to the climate on a psychological and emotional level. Much of Kudsk Steensen’s work is rooted in the sociological idea that we no longer live in an era where the future can be predicted based on the past, and that technology and nature are transforming faster and more drastically than we are able to grasp. He creates poetic interpretations about overlooked natural phenomena through collaborations with field biologists, composers and writers. His works range from immersive VR ecosystems to mixed reality installations bridging physical and digital worlds, which invite audiences to enter new ecological realities. Kudsk Steensen was a finalist for the Future Generation Art Prize at the 2019 Venice Biennale, and he was the recipient of the Best Production Design award for RE-ANIMATED (2019) at the Cinequest Festival for Technology and Cinema. Kudsk Steensen is currently an Artist-in-Residence at Luma Arles in France, where he is documenting algae and crystallization processes across the Camargue wetland.\r\n								</div>[imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00017.jpg\" alt=\"Jakob Kudsk Steensen - The Deep Listener\"><figcaption class=\"caption caption-roman\">Jakob Kudsk Steensen - The Deep Listener</figcaption></figure>[endimagedivider][imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00018.jpg\" alt=\"Jakob Kudsk Steensen - Re-Animated\"><figcaption class=\"caption caption-roman\">Jakob Kudsk Steensen - Re-Animated</figcaption></figure>[endimagedivider][imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00019.jpg\" alt=\"Jakob Kudsk Steensen - Catharsis\"><figcaption class=\"caption caption-roman\">Jakob Kudsk Steensen - Catharsis</figcaption></figure>[endimagedivider][imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00020.jpg\" alt=\"Jakob Kudsk Steensen - Catharsis installation\"><figcaption class=\"caption caption-roman\">Jakob Kudsk Steensen - Catharsis installation</figcaption></figure>[endimagedivider][sectiondivider]Camille Henrot[sectiontitledivider]Camille Henrot 1978年出生于法国巴黎，现生活和工作于纽约，她的艺术实践在电影、绘画、绘画、雕塑和装置艺术之间无缝切换。Henrot的作品反映了对哲学、文学和人类学的兴趣，她创作的过程通常少不了详尽的研究。“作为一名艺术家，我拥有以外行者的好奇心而阅览各种理论的自由，” 她曾说：“我能够以非理性的方式获取知识，这种特权足以让我很感激。我把世界视为一个破碎的整体，而这种破碎是令人痛心的。通过作品里所隐含的研究内容，我就可以建立某种连续性。”信息分配模式和人际联系方式的变化、个体经验与宏观动力学的关系、图像与语言的关系，这些都是 Henrot 的作品核心。她关注的是直面情绪和政治问题，并着眼于探讨意识形态、全球化、信仰和新媒体是如何相互作用从而创造出一种“结构性焦虑”(structural anxiety)的环境。Henrot 的近期个展将于墨尔本维多利亚国家美术馆(2021年)和安特卫普 Middelheim 博物馆(2022年)开幕。<div><br>Camille Henrot was born in 1978 in Paris, France. She lives and works in New York. Her practice moves seamlessly between film, painting, drawing, sculpture and installation. Henrot’s work reflects her interest in philosophy, literature, and anthropology; her creative process often involves exhaustive research. “As an artist, I have the freedom to browse through ideas with the curiosity of the amateur,” she once said. “I’m allowed to have an irrational approach to knowledge, which is a privilege I appreciate a lot. I see the world as a fragmented ensemble and that fragmentation is harrowing. Through the research implied by my projects, I can establish some continuity.” Henrot is interested in confronting emotional and political issues, and looking at how ideology, globalization, belief and new media are interacting to create an environment of structural anxiety. The changing modes of information distribution and interpersonal connections, the relationships between individual experiences and macroscopic dynamics, as well as between images and language, are at the center of her works. Upcoming solo exhibitions include the National Gallery of Victoria, Melbourne, Australia (2021), and Middelheim Museum (2022).\r\n								</div>[imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00021.jpg\" alt=\"Camille Henrot - Grosse Fatigue\"><figcaption class=\"caption caption-roman\">Camille Henrot - Grosse Fatigue</figcaption></figure>[endimagedivider][imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00022.jpg\"></figure>[endimagedivider][imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00023.jpg\"></figure>[endimagedivider][imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00024.jpg\"></figure>[endimagedivider][sectiondivider]test[sectiontitledivider]test[sectiondivider]',NULL),(18,1,'2021-02-02 09:30:59','2021-02-02 10:16:07',NULL,'Artist Panel Talk, Screening[tagdivider]Lee Kai Chung ⌁ Wang Tuo',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'lee-kai-chung-wang-tuo',NULL,'2020-04-24 19:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Zoom online meeting',_binary '[imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00025.png\" alt=\"Wang Tuo - 烟火\"><figcaption class=\"caption caption-roman\">Wang Tuo - 烟火</figcaption></figure>[endimagedivider][imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media/00026.png\" alt=\"共谋失忆症\"><figcaption class=\"caption caption-roman\">共谋失忆症</figcaption></figure>[endimagedivider]<div class=\"centered\">Screening List:<br><em>《烟火》《共谋失忆症》</em></div>[sectiondivider]',NULL),(19,1,'2021-02-03 02:06:24','2021-02-03 03:55:30',NULL,'Critique Marathon[tagdivider]Round One',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'round-one',NULL,'2020-05-22 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Zoom online meeting',_binary '<div class=\"centered\"><a href=\"https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/NfeLRruiktFI7x4I-yCggA\" target=\"_blank\">活动信息</a></div>[imagedivider]<figure class=\"body-image-holder\"><img src=\"//trigggggggger.local/media